description: The target index is comprised of equity securities of U.S. companies in the highest quintile of the average twelve month trailing dividend yield over each of the prior four quarters in the S&P 900, and that rank in the top half of their respective GICS sector classification. The fund may use either a replication strategy or representative sampling strategy in seeking to track the performance of the target index. It will primarily invest in U.S. companies that are included in the target index.
name: Global Beta Smart Income ETF
